{"author":{"id":"c4712575109c327bdd55aba22ffc85056a57c52d1f733268a7aaae0da808160e"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1552341379,"nonce":"r8OaxqMODuXiNbX3hkm0Bd87qwU=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0MTk3MDI3MDg=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2327","origin":"github"},"title":"Diffbind with EdgeR","message":"[The galaxy Diffbind tool](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/diffbind/diffbind.xml) doesn't seem to have an option to use EdgeR instead of DESeq2 underneath. The galaxy Diffbind tool markdown says: \n\n\u003e it uses statistical routines developed in an RNA-Seq context (primarily the Bioconductor packages edgeR and DESeq2)\n\n\u003e the core analysis routines are executed, by default using DESeq2\n\nBut the option to use EdgeR is not surfaced. From the [Diffbind docs](http://bioconductor.org/packages/release/bioc/vignettes/DiffBind/inst/doc/DiffBind.pdf) (section 7.4): \n\n\u003e When `dba.analyze` is invoked using the default `method=DBA_EDGER`, a standardized differential analysis is performed using the edgeR package.\n\nThat should be an option passed to this line: \n\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/a0c51ab52c4e3f296d5577ee3af26c4c1465e1e9/tools/diffbind/diffbind.R#L81","files":null}]}